other_tests.findings: Horizontal ST-segment depressions of 1 mm in the inferior leads.

Normal left ventricular ejection fraction; subtle hypokinesis of the inferior wall; mild hypertrophy in the left ventricle; two masses with heterogeneous echotexture compressing the tricuspid annulus.
Two aneurysmal segments of the underlying graft, one measuring 4.4 cm and the other 4.0 cm, compressing the right atrioventricular groove, tricuspid annulus, and right ventricle.
Presence of two masses compressing the tricuspid annulus and right atrium.
